Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Strong support from neighbourhood planner along with successful community and city process has led to the opportunity for multifamily development up to 18-units at 956 Notre Dame Avenue. A Partnership Agreement has been papered with Peg City Car Co-op and architectural drawings and structural plans are in place. 956 Notre Dame Avenue is adjacent to Health Sciences Centre, Women’s Hospital, CancerCare Manitoba and Manitoba Clinic. The property is also in close proximity to University of Winnipeg, University of Manitoba Bannatyne Campus and Cindy Klassen Recreation Complex.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The presented parcel of land is located adjacent to the boundary of City of Winnipeg and the Rural Municipality of MacDonald. The 1.97 acre site is an excellent location for the small business owner or developer looking to be located close to the major trucking routes, the Kenaston Retail node and major developing and existing residential/commercial areas. The big box stores are only ~2.5 kilometers away.  Both adjacent properties are developed and the utilities are located at the property line.  This is a great opportunity to invest in your business. There are no business taxes and the zoning allows for a large variety of permitted uses.
